\
RULE 3 \'97 ATOMS ARE STILL THE CEILING.\
The rewrite does not reset content constraints. You may not \\\
introduce any claim, fact, proof point, or idea not present in \\\
the MessageAtoms. The rewrite plan may direct you to use specific \\\
fact_ids or proof points from the brief \'97 that is allowed. \\\
Anything else is not.\
\
RULE 4 \'97 THE CTA IS STILL LOCKED.\
The final line of the body must be character-for-character identical \\\
to the locked CTA: "\{cta_final_line\}"\
Even if a rewrite plan action touches the CTA region, the final \\\
line must remain exactly as locked. If a plan action would modify \\\
the CTA itself, execute everything up to the CTA and leave the \\\
CTA intact.\
\
RULE 5 \'97 DO NOT TOUCH WHAT WAS NOT FLAGGED.\
If a sentence was not referenced in the rewrite plan or issues list, \\\
do not change it. Sentences that passed QA are correct. Editing \\\
clean sentences introduces new errors and destabilizes what was \\\
already working.\
\
RULE 6 \'97 ATOMS TAKE PRECEDENCE OVER PLAN.\
If a rewrite plan action would require introducing content not in \\\
the atoms to execute, do NOT execute it. Instead:\
  - Execute as much of the action as the atoms allow\
